Muscle release and emotional release can go hand in hand, and they're super common during your stretch session. We often don’t have time to really tap into our emotions during our day-to-day, but when you lay on my table, you focus on the internal for once. 🤍

Our myofascial tissue, or the connective tissue around our muscles, is a sensory organ, and this tissue actually contains sensory nerves, which means that emotions can be stored in our muscles. By stretching your muscles, you release all the trapped emotions during “somato-emotional release” (“soma” stands for body). Sometimes even trauma. You also opening your chakras 🪬

If you get hit with a sudden rush of feels, explore it. Embrace the moment. It’s powerful healing. You are here to find mind-body balance too. 😌
